SIMPLE: forthright
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Forthright
<hw>Forth"right`</hw> <pr>(? ⟦or⟧ ?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Forth</ets>, <pos>adv.</pos> + <ets>right</ets>,
<pos>adv.</pos>]</ety> <def>Straight forward; in a straight
direction.</def> <mark>[Archaic]</mark> <rj><au>Sir P.
Sidney.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Forthright</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Forthright
<hw>Forth"right`</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Direct; straightforward;
<as>as, a <ex>forthright</ex> man</as>.</def> <mark>[Archaic]</mark>
<rj><au>Lowell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They were Night and Day, and Day and Night,⟦br⟧
Piligrims wight with steps <qex>forthright</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Emerson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Forthright</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Forthright
<hw>Forth"right`</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A straight path.</def>
<mark>[Archaic]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Here's a maze trod, indeed,⟦br⟧
Through <qex>forthrights</qex> and meanders!</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Forthrightness</ent>⟦br⟧
